to  submit their research for publication in scholarly journals  There are numerous research opportunities both at VMI and at other institutions  Usually  a research project may span one or two years in duration with the bulk of a student s research being conducted over one or two summers  During the summer  students are often paid a stipend similar to some internships  If you are interested in getting involved in a project talk to your academic advisor for more information  Other resources  Career Services Faculty Research Interests Database Learn more about External Undergraduate Research Opportunities at institutions outside VMI   Undergraduate Research  How to Begin Presenting Research Get Published   VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 